<!-- Introduction Section -->
<section class="intro">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Canada, the second-largest country in the world by land area, is known for its diverse landscapes, rich culture, and warm-hearted people. From the stunning natural beauty of the Canadian Rockies and Niagara Falls to the charming streets of Old Quebec City, Canada offers something for every traveler. It is also famous for its delicious food, including iconic dishes like poutine and maple syrup. Whether you're an outdoor enthusiast or a foodie, Canada has something to captivate your heart.</p>
    <p>The country's vast wilderness is home to some of the most breathtaking national parks and wildlife, including polar bears, moose, and beavers. Canada is also a land of multiculturalism, where different ethnic groups come together to create a harmonious and inclusive society. The cities, such as Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal, are vibrant cultural hubs, offering a blend of modern architecture, art, and entertainment. Whether you are hiking in Banff, enjoying the winter sports in Whistler, or experiencing the unique blend of French and English heritage in Montreal, Canada provides endless opportunities for adventure and discovery.</p>
    <p>Moreover, Canada is famous for its commitment to peace, human rights, and environmental sustainability, making it a beacon of hope on the world stage. From its iconic maple leaf to its friendly people, Canada truly stands out as a country that celebrates diversity, nature, and community. No matter where you visit in Canada, you are sure to feel the warmth and welcoming spirit that defines this beautiful nation.</p>
</section>

